PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1783703991
OL,3,C'A privilege': Arthur Fery's former
OL,4,Ccoach ahead of Wimbledon quarter-final
OL,6,F"He doesn't need my advice. But it is
OL,7,Fclear to me that he is, despite all
OL,8,Fthe things going on around him,
OL,9,Fdespite how overwhelming all of this
OL,10,Fis, he is focusing on the task at hand.
OL,12,F"Arthur is taking it one point at a
OL,13,Ftime, he isn't looking ahead. He can't
OL,14,Fbe paying attention to the wonderful
OL,15,Fnoise around him and it is all
OL,16,Fwonderful and it's so well earned but
OL,17,Fwhile he's still at Wimbledon stay
OL,18,Ffocused on the task at hand and I know
OL,19,Fhe's doing that."
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/8
